elements.title: Ethel Ogden (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Canadian painter Ethel Ogden (pictured) was central to developing china painting within the Fine Arts Department at the Mount Allison Ladies' College?

elements.title: Arlington County Board v. Richards (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that in Arlington County Board v. Richards, the U.S. Supreme Court considered the constitutionality of one of the first American residential zoned parking programs?

elements.title: Ulf Merbold (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Ulf Merbold, the first West German in space, grew up in East Germany?

elements.title: Julian M. Wright (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that judge advocate Julian M. Wright was once a fencer, and President Theodore Roosevelt attended one of his matches in 1902?

elements.title: Ulmus chuchuanus (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Ulmus chuchuanus had to be renamed due to another fossil already having its original name?

elements.title: Maks Levin (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that a photograph by Maks Levin, showing destroyed buildings in Kyiv, was featured on the cover of a March 2022 edition of the German magazine Der Spiegel?

elements.title: CJVB (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that to convince Canadian regulators that Vancouver could support a new ethnic radio station, the founder of CJVB documented local restaurants and Sikh temples?

elements.title: the Chinatown of Phoenix, Arizona (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that most of the Chinese in the Chinatown of Phoenix, Arizona, had emigrated from the same village in China's Hoiping County?
